verses.roman:
kibā yukti kaila duṅhe, keha nāhi jāne
phale anumāna pāche kaila bhakta-gaṇe

synonyms: kibā yukti kaila—what consultation They had; duṅhe—both of Them; keha nāhi jāne—no one knows; phale—by the result; anumāna—guess; pāche—later; kaila—did; bhakta-gaṇe—all the devotees.
translation: No one could understand what the brothers discussed between Themselves, but later all the devotees could guess what the subject matter was.
